# YAML API Documentation Requirements

## MANDATORY Documentation Rules
- **Generate YAML documentation for ALL new API endpoints**
- **Create YAML files simultaneously with controller implementation**
- **File Location**: [backend/src/main/resources/yaml/](mdc:backend/src/main/resources/yaml/)
- **Documentation Format**: OpenAPI/Swagger 3.0 specification

## File Structure
```
backend/src/main/resources/yaml/
├── user-role-api.yaml
├── test-case-set-api.yaml
└── README.md
```

## YAML File Requirements
- **File Naming**: Use descriptive names (e.g., `{module}-api.yaml`)
- **File Size**: Each YAML file must not exceed 200 lines
- **Content Structure**: Follow OpenAPI 3.0 specification
- **Language**: Use English for documentation
- **Examples**: Include request/response examples

## Required YAML Content
```yaml
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  title: API Title
  version: 1.0.0
  description: API Description
paths:
  /api/endpoint:
    get:
      summary: Endpoint description
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Success response
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResponseModel'
components:
  schemas:
    ResponseModel:
      type: object
      properties:
        field: {type: string}
```

## Documentation Standards
- Include all HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Document request parameters and body schemas
- Document response schemas and status codes
- Include error response documentation
- Provide example requests and responses
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Document file upload endpoints with multipart/form-data

## File Upload Documentation
- Document supported file formats (.zip, .tar.gz)
- Specify file size limits (100MB)
- Document filename format requirements
- Include Content-Type headers for downloads
- Document file format validation rules